# Infrastructure — Cloudflare Workers Model

The entire backend is **one Cloudflare Worker**, configured by `wrangler.toml`
and deployed with `wrangler`. There is no CDK, no Lambda, no API Gateway, no
Secrets Manager, no CodeDeploy. The Worker IS the edge (Cloudflare WAF/DDoS/CDN
are account-level platform config, not code).

## wrangler.toml (single source of infra truth)
- `name`, `main = "src/node/worker.ts"`, `compatibility_date`, `compatibility_flags = ["nodejs_compat"]` (nodejs_compat + a 2025+ date populate `process.env` from `[vars]` + secrets, so `process.env.X` reads work).
- `[observability]` — Workers Logs (replaces CloudWatch).
- `[triggers] crons = [...]` — Cron Triggers; expressions are the DISPATCH KEYS and must match the keys of `cronRegistry` in `src/node/cron.ts` byte-for-byte. `[triggers]` IS inherited by named envs, so it is declared once at top level.
- `[vars]` — **non-secret** config (NODE_ENV, STAGE, PROJECT_NAME, API_VERSION, CORS_* lists, IMAGES_BUCKET, IMAGES_CDN_URL, SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT). `[vars]` and `[[r2_buckets]]` are NOT inherited by named envs — they are repeated in full under `[env.staging]`/`[env.production]`. Never put secrets here.
- `[[r2_buckets]] binding = "IMAGES"` — R2 media bucket (replaces the S3 images bucket); route code reaches it as `c.env.IMAGES`. `bucket_name` must match `IMAGES_BUCKET`. `wrangler dev --local` simulates it on disk under `.wrangler/state`.
- `[env.staging]` / `[env.production]` — each repeats `*.vars` and `*.r2_buckets`.

## Adding infra
- **New binding** (R2/KV/Queue/etc.): declare it in `wrangler.toml` (top level AND every `[env.*]` block), add the property to `WorkerBindings` in `src/node/worker.ts`, and extend `AppEnv["Bindings"]` (lib/hono/types.ts) so routes see `c.env.<NAME>` typed.
- **New cron job**: add the cron expression to `[triggers].crons` AND a same-key entry to `cronRegistry` in `src/node/cron.ts` (a mismatch throws by design). Job bodies live in `src/node/handlers/utils/` and MUST throw on failure (a swallowed error records a false success). `worker.ts` `scheduled` dispatches by exact cron string.
- **New secret**: add the name to `.dev.vars.example` (the checked-in registry), set it locally in `.dev.vars`, and push it with `pnpm sync-secrets <stage>` (`wrangler secret put`). Values travel over stdin only.
- **New non-secret var**: add to `[vars]` and to each `[env.*].vars`.

## Secrets & config
- Secrets: `.dev.vars` locally (gitignored), `wrangler secret put` deployed (driven by `pnpm sync-secrets <stage>` from `.env.<stage>` over the `.dev.vars.example` registry). Never plaintext credentials in code or committed files.
- `pnpm migrate` / drizzle-kit read `DATABASE_URL` from `.env.local` (dotenv), not `.dev.vars` — keep both in sync.
- Media S3-API path needs `R2_ACCOUNT_ID`, `R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` (presigned via `aws4fetch` in `lib/media.ts`); unset → media routes return a clear 503 `MEDIA_STORAGE_NOT_CONFIGURED`.
- Do NOT reintroduce Lambda-era toggles (`ORIGIN_VERIFY_SECRET`, `ENABLE_WAF`) — gone by construction.

## Deploy (scripts/)
- **Local:** `pnpm dev` (`wrangler dev --local`, port 8787) — no Cloudflare account; R2/cron simulated on disk.
- **Deploy:** `pnpm deploy:staging` / `pnpm deploy:production` run `scripts/deploy.ts`, a **health-gated gradual rollout with automatic rollback** (records the active version → uploads the new version at 0% → canary split + soak → promotes to 100% → probes `/v1/health/detailed` at each gate → any failure redeploys the prior version and exits 1). First deploy goes straight to 100%. The plain `wrangler deploy --env <stage>` lives at `pnpm deploy:{staging,production}:simple`.
- **Migrations are a separate step** from code deploy (`pnpm migrate` against the stage DB) — expand/contract-safe per release (AGENTS.md invariant 12).
- **Rollback:** `npx wrangler rollback --env <stage>` (Workers keeps prior versions); `scripts/deploy.ts` also auto-rolls-back a failed canary/promotion.

## Local cron testing
`npx wrangler dev --local --test-scheduled`, then
`curl "http://localhost:8787/__scheduled?cron=0+4+*+*+*"` (janitor) /
`cron=0+5+*+*+*` (audit retention).
